column1: #Text=Chibemba or Bemba is a Bantu language spoken in Zambia , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , and southern Tanzania .
#Text=It is the biggest ethnic grouping in Zambia , accounting for over 50 % of the Zambian population .
#Text=Bemba people ( Ababemba ) trace their origin from " KOLA " in Angola .
#Text=The writing system is very phonetic and Spanish speakers would find it very easy to learn .
#Text=Many Bemba words can also be found in Swahili .
